description: Retrieves the policy that was generated using StartPolicyGeneration.

parameters.name: jobId
parameters.description: The JobId that is returned by the StartPolicyGeneration operation. The JobId can be used with GetGeneratedPolicy to retrieve the generated policies or used with CancelPolicyGeneration to cancel the policy generation request. The JobId can be used with GetGeneratedPolicy to retrieve the generated policies or used with CancelPolicyGeneration to cancel the policy generation request.

parameters.name: includeResourcePlaceholders
parameters.description:
The level of detail that you want to generate. You can specify whether to generate policies with placeholders for resource ARNs for actions that support resource level granularity in policies.
For example, in the resource section of a policy, you can receive a placeholder such as "Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}" instead of "*". You can specify whether to generate policies with placeholders for resource ARNs for actions that support resource level granularity in policies. For example, in the resource section of a policy, you can receive a placeholder such as "Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}" instead of "*".

parameters.name: includeServiceLevelTemplate
parameters.description:
The level of detail that you want to generate. You can specify whether to generate service-level policies.
IAM Access Analyzer uses iam:servicelastaccessed to identify services that have been used recently to create this service-level template. You can specify whether to generate service-level policies. nested_items.name: jobDetails
nested_items.description: A GeneratedPolicyDetails object that contains details about the generated policy.

nested_items.name: jobId
nested_items.description: The JobId that is returned by the StartPolicyGeneration operation. The JobId can be used with GetGeneratedPolicy to retrieve the generated policies or used with CancelPolicyGeneration to cancel the policy generation request.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the job request.

nested_items.name: startedOn
nested_items.description: A timestamp of when the job was started.

nested_items.name: completedOn
nested_items.description: A timestamp of when the job was completed.

nested_items.name: code
nested_items.description: The job error code.

nested_items.name: message
nested_items.description: Specific information about the error. For example, which service quota was exceeded or which resource was not found.

nested_items.name: generatedPolicyResult
nested_items.description: A GeneratedPolicyResult object that contains the generated policies and associated details.

nested_items.name: properties
nested_items.description: A GeneratedPolicyProperties object that contains properties of the generated policy.

nested_items.name: isComplete
nested_items.description: This value is set to true if the generated policy contains all possible actions for a service that IAM Access Analyzer identified from the CloudTrail trail that you specified, and false otherwise.

nested_items.name: principalArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the IAM entity (user or role) for which you are generating a policy.

nested_items.name: cloudTrailProperties
nested_items.description: Lists details about the Trail used to generated policy.

nested_items.name: trailProperties
nested_items.description: A TrailProperties object that contains settings for trail properties.

nested_items.name: cloudTrailArn
nested_items.description: Specifies the ARN of the trail. The format of a trail ARN is arn:aws:cloudtrail:us-east-2:123456789012:trail/MyTrail.

nested_items.name: regions
nested_items.description: A list of regions to get CloudTrail data from and analyze to generate a policy.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: allRegions
nested_items.description: Possible values are true or false. If set to true, IAM Access Analyzer retrieves CloudTrail data from all regions to analyze and generate a policy.

nested_items.name: startTime
nested_items.description: The start of the time range for which IAM Access Analyzer reviews your CloudTrail events. Events with a timestamp before this time are not considered to generate a policy.

nested_items.name: endTime
nested_items.description: The end of the time range for which IAM Access Analyzer reviews your CloudTrail events. Events with a timestamp after this time are not considered to generate a policy. If this is not included in the request, the default value is the current time.

nested_items.name: generatedPolicies
nested_items.description: The text to use as the content for the new policy. The policy is created using the CreatePolicy action.

nested_items.name: policy
nested_items.description: The text to use as the content for the new policy. The policy is created using the CreatePolicy action.
